---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';

const phoneDisplay = '054-339-5560';
const phoneHref = '+972543395560';
const whatsappHref = 'https://wa.me/972543395560';

const trustHighlights = [
  {
    value: '10+',
    label: 'Years of experience',
    description: 'Deep experience in large-scale projects, complex buildings, and private homes.',
  },
  {
    value: 'Beyond',
    label: 'Flagship project',
    description: 'Part of the planning team behind one of Israel’s most iconic and complex developments.',
  },
  {
    value: 'Boutique',
    label: 'Personal guidance',
    description: 'A boutique studio offering attentive listening, planning precision, and full personal availability.',
  },
];

const testimonials = [
  {
    quote:
      'Choosing Chani came naturally to me, after all she is my daughter. When we decided to renovate the kitchen for the second time and add a safe room, Chani stepped in immediately. Unlike an earlier renovation where our needs were not heard well enough, she handled everything with outstanding professionalism and humanity. She listened to my dreams and helped bring them to life without compromising practicality or comfort. The renovation moved quickly, with very little time to prepare in advance, and still everything was done with calm and confidence. Chani introduced planning solutions and ideas I had never known before, and today I cannot imagine managing without them. She made sure everything was carried out in the best possible way. I have no doubt that whenever I need to in the future, I will choose her again.',
    author: 'Avishag Ehrlich',
    role: 'Kitchen design, Jerusalem',
    image: '/trust-kitchen.png',
    imageAlt:
      'A white kitchen with clean millwork, a natural wood accent at the center, stone surfaces, and a refined minimalist feel.',
    tag: 'Private project',
  },
  {
    quote:
      'Architect Chani Berger was part of the planning team for the Beyond project initiated by Tidhar, a project I managed. From knowing her both professionally and personally, I can say with full confidence that she is a high-caliber, hardworking, and exceptionally bright professional. Chani handled every task in the project, large and small, with initiative and genuine motivation to improve both the planning process and the final result. She is proactive, devoted, and committed to meeting goals at the highest level of quality. Alongside all of this, Chani is pleasant, intelligent, and brings excellent judgment and interpersonal skills. She integrated perfectly into the planning team and earned deep appreciation from the colleagues and managers who worked with her. I wish Chani great success in every path she chooses.',
    author: 'Galit Gat Horowitz',
    role: 'VP of Quality, Management Division - Tidhar',
    image: '/trust-beyond.jpg',
    imageAlt:
      'An aerial rendering of the Beyond project with illuminated glass towers in the heart of the metropolitan skyline.',
    tag: 'Mega project',
  },
  {
    quote:
      'I would like to recommend Chani Berger, a talented young architect who worked alongside me on the "Savyonei HaShmura" urban renewal project by Africa Israel Residences, a large-scale project that included the planning of 512 housing units, public buildings, and commercial spaces. During our work together, Chani demonstrated exceptional diligence, thoroughness, and professionalism. She approached every aspect of the project with an energetic and committed attitude, showing full responsibility and precise, creative planning skills. Beyond her impressive professional abilities, she is a pleasant, service-oriented professional who knows how to listen, understand needs, and work fruitfully with all parties involved – planners and consultants alike. Work of the highest level, with personal and dedicated guidance all along the way.',
    author: 'Dekel Rukban',
    role: 'Project Manager, Africa Israel Residences',
    image: '/trust-savyoney.jpg',
    imageAlt: 'A visualization of the Savyonei HaShmura project with white residential towers',
    tag: 'Mega project',
  },
  {
    quote:
      'I warmly recommend Chani Berger, who works with me as a planner opposite the Gabay Group. During our work together, I had the privilege of getting to know a professional, talented, and highly motivated woman who brings added value to every project she is involved in. Chani has shown exceptional abilities in architecture, both from a planning and a creative perspective. She handles challenges calmly, finding efficient and innovative solutions. She also excels in teamwork and maintains positive, effective communication with all parties involved in the projects. As a senior project manager, I can attest to Chani Berger’s significant contribution to the success of our projects. Thanks to her extensive professional knowledge, alongside her responsible and dedicated approach, she consistently meets deadlines and delivers the highest quality results. I recommend her wholeheartedly for any future role or project, confident she will be a meaningful asset to any organization or team lucky enough to work with her.',
    author: 'Nofar Shraga',
    role: 'Senior Project Manager, Gabay Group',
    image: '/trust-gabai.jpg',
    imageAlt: 'Visualization of a modern residential project with two towers',
    tag: 'Architectural planning',
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Alma | Architecture & Interior Design"
  description="Alma Studio by Chani Berger creates architecture and interior design with natural materials, planning precision, and a grounded, lasting sense of home."
>
  <Navbar />

  <main id="main-content" tabindex="-1" class="bg-white text-black">
    <section id="home" class="relative min-h-screen w-full overflow-hidden" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
      <div class="absolute inset-0">
        <div id="parallax-bg" class="absolute inset-0 h-[115%] -top-[15%] w-full will-change-transform">
          <img
            src="/hero-new.jpg"
            alt="A monochromatic living room in soft tones with a built-in bench, tall windows, wooden shelves, and a woman seated by the window."
            class="w-full h-full object-cover object-[center_65%] animate-ken-burns grayscale saturate-0 contrast-110 brightness-90"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/20 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="relative z-10 min-h-screen flex flex-col p-8 md:p-16 pb-12">
        <div class="max-w-[90vw] flex-1 flex flex-col justify-center md:justify-start md:pt-[14vh]">
          <div class="text-white">
            <div
              class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-6 md:gap-x-12 text-3xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-light opacity-90 mb-8 md:mb-20 font-cardo"
              aria-label="Material, meaning, form"
            >
              <span class="reveal-text" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">Material.</span>
              <span class="reveal-text" style="animation-delay: 0.2s">Meaning.</span>
              <span class="reveal-text" style="animation-delay: 0.3s">Form.</span>
            </div>

            <h1
              id="hero-title"
              class="text-white text-7xl md:text-[13vw] leading-[0.78] md:leading-[0.75] font-bold tracking-tighter reveal-text"
              style="animation-delay: 0.4s"
            >
              Alma.
            </h1>

            <p
              class="text-lg md:text-3xl mt-8 md:mt-20 opacity-90 font-light tracking-[0.08em] reveal-text font-cardo"
              style="animation-delay: 0.6s"
            >
              Architecture between people and place.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="portfolio"
      class="py-32 px-8 md:px-16 bg-white overflow-hidden"
      aria-labelledby="portfolio-heading"
    >
      <div class="max-w-[1800px] mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-20 md:mb-32 border-b border-black/5 pb-10 md:pb-14">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:justify-between md:items-end gap-8 md:gap-12">
            <div class="max-w-2xl">
              <p class="text-xs md:text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-stone-600 mb-5">
                Gallery of Vision
              </p>
              <h2
                id="portfolio-heading"
                class="text-5xl md:text-9xl font-light tracking-tighter text-black"
              >
                Alma
              </h2>
            </div>
            <p class="max-w-md text-lg md:text-xl text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed">
              An architectural language moving between material, light, and precision. Every frame reflects
              the same worldview through a different moment of stillness, presence, and depth.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-16 md:gap-x-12 md:gap-y-40">
          <div class="md:col-span-5 group relative">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-8 md:max-w-[32rem]">
              <img
                src="/Screenshot 2025-12-26 at 0.40.22.png"
                alt="A minimalist living space in warm tones with a light sofa, natural walls, and clean lines."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-md md:pl-6">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 01</span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-light mb-4">Organic minimalism</h3>
              <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                A meeting point between disciplined geometry, natural materials, and softer forms. Spaces
                designed to breathe alongside the people who live in them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-7 md:mt-32 group relative">
            <div class="aspect-[16/9] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-8 md:max-w-[46rem] md:mr-0 md:ml-auto">
              <img
                src="/Screenshot 2025-12-26 at 0.40.33.png"
                alt="A bright interior with tall openings, soft natural light, and pale surfaces that emphasize the volume of the space."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-sm md:ml-12">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 02</span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-light mb-4">A dialogue with light</h3>
              <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                Light is the most transparent material in the design process. It is used to sculpt space and
                give it shifting depth throughout the day.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-5 group relative">
            <div class="aspect-[4/5] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-8 md:max-w-[30rem]">
              <img
                src="/Screenshot 2025-12-26 at 0.40.41.png"
                alt="An interior corner with precise millwork, integrated shelving, and a gentle meeting of wood, stone, and plaster."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-sm md:pl-6">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 03</span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-light mb-4">Architecture of details</h3>
              <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                The whole is greater than the sum of its parts only when every part is handled with care.
                Bespoke joinery, material junctions, and millimeter-level precision matter.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-7 md:-mt-32 group relative">
            <div class="aspect-[16/10] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-8 shadow-2xl md:z-10 relative md:max-w-[48rem] md:mr-0 md:ml-auto">
              <img
                src="/Screenshot 2025-12-26 at 0.40.53.png"
                alt="A balanced living space combining natural stone, dark wood, soft furnishings, and gentle lighting."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-md md:ml-14">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 04</span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-light mb-4">Materials that feel alive</h3>
              <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                Natural stone, brushed oak, and exposed metal. Materials are chosen to age with dignity and
                tell a story of authenticity and connection to the earth.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-12 group relative border-t border-black/5 pt-32">
            <div class="aspect-[21/9] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-12 md:max-w-[72rem] md:mx-auto">
              <img
                src="/Screenshot 2025-12-26 at 0.41.01.png"
                alt="A calm sculpted bathroom with natural stone, broad surfaces, and soft diffused lighting."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-start gap-8">
              <div class="max-w-xl">
                <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 05</span>
                <h3 class="text-5xl font-light mb-6">A sanctuary of quiet</h3>
                <p class="text-2xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                  Bathrooms and wellness spaces that become a retreat from the outside world. Natural stone
                  and clean lines create an atmosphere of complete calm.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="h-[1px] w-full md:w-64 bg-black self-end mb-4" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-6 group relative">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-8 md:max-w-[31rem]">
              <img
                src="/WhatsApp Image 2025-12-26 at 01.38.00.jpeg"
                alt="A welcoming entry hall with warm materials, calm geometric lines, and inviting light."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-md md:pl-6">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 06</span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-light mb-4">The first encounter</h3>
              <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                Entry spaces that combine warm materials with inviting geometry, creating a gentle transition
                from outside to in.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="md:col-span-6 md:mt-32 group relative">
            <div class="aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100 mb-8 md:max-w-[31rem] md:mr-0 md:ml-auto">
              <img
                src="/WhatsApp Image 2025-12-26 at 01.40.12.jpeg"
                alt="A dark minimalist kitchen with deep wooden fronts, a central island, and a natural stone surface."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[2s] group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-md md:ml-12">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-600 mb-2 block tracking-widest">STYLE 07</span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-light mb-4">Restrained drama</h3>
              <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
                Kitchens shaped by dark, disciplined minimalism. Deep wood textures paired with natural stone
                create a timeless and luxurious expression.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="about"
      class="py-32 md:py-48 px-8 md:px-16 max-w-[1800px] mx-auto"
      aria-labelledby="about-heading"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-24 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 md:sticky md:top-32">
          <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-stone-600 mb-8 block">
            The Studio
          </span>
          <h2 id="about-heading" class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-light leading-tight mb-12">
            Quiet design,<br />
            lasting presence.
          </h2>
          <div class="h-[1px] w-24 bg-black mb-12" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <span class="text-lg font-medium">Chani Berger</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-stone-700 uppercase tracking-widest">Lead Architect</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 flex flex-col gap-32">
          <div class="relative group">
            <div class="overflow-hidden mb-8 aspect-[4/5] max-w-lg">
              <img
                src="/Chani.jpg"
                alt="Portrait of Chani Berger, architect and interior designer, standing in a bright space with natural light."
                class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[1.5s] ease-out group-hover:scale-105"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="md:pr-24 max-w-2xl space-y-8">
              <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-800">
                At Alma Studio, I believe architecture and interior design are far more than the creation of a
                beautiful space. They are a way of shaping a place that holds belonging, presence, quiet, and
                depth. My vision is to create homes and environments that feel truly right: precisely attuned to
                the people who live in them, their way of life, and the way they want to feel every day. I believe
                in rooted architecture, connected to the earth, to material, to time, and to people. Not architecture
                that chases trends or momentary gestures, but work that seeks strong foundations, timeless beauty,
                and a simplicity that carries depth.
              </p>
              <p class="text-lg font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-800">
                For me, good design begins with genuine listening: listening to people, to their habits, to what is
                said and to what is not always easy to put into words. From that listening, a precise, sensitive,
                and deeply personal process takes shape, where every decision grows from meaning rather than
                appearance alone. I believe in honest materiality, natural tones, clean but never cold lines, and
                spaces that feel both stable and soft, refined yet alive.
              </p>
              <p class="text-lg font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-800">
                The values that guide me are truth, precision, attentiveness, craft, simplicity, warmth, and loyalty
                to place, not only as a physical location, but as a deep feeling of home. I aim to create spaces for
                my clients that bring order, breath, and balance; spaces that allow real life to unfold within them
                through quiet, effortless beauty. Alma, to me, is a complete philosophy: a meeting of material and
                emotion, of practicality and aesthetics, of home as a structure and home as a feeling. It is design
                intended to hold full lives, family, hospitality, routine, growth, and memory, and give them a
                framework that feels exact, natural, and enduring.
              </p>

              <div class="pt-8 border-t border-black/10">
                <p class="text-lg font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-800 mb-6">
                  The studio is backed by more than a decade of experience in mega-projects and complex buildings.
                  Chani played a leading planning role in iconic developments such as
                  <strong class="font-normal"> Beyond (Tidhar)</strong>, the flagship Givatayim project that
                  combines a 70-story office tower with a 45-story residential tower.
                </p>
                <p class="text-base font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
                  Her professional background, developed at the leading firm
                  <strong class="font-normal"> Barel Levitzky Kassif (B.L.K)</strong>, also includes large-scale
                  projects such as Savyonei HaSharon in Netanya and the HaGdud HaIvri project. Today, those
                  strategic planning abilities and international team leadership skills are translated into a boutique
                  studio that offers personal attention and uncompromising architectural precision.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="values"
      class="py-32 px-8 md:px-16 max-w-[1800px] mx-auto border-t border-black/5"
      aria-labelledby="values-heading"
    >
      <div class="mb-24 flex justify-between items-end gap-8">
        <h2 id="values-heading" class="text-4xl md:text-8xl font-light tracking-tighter">Core values</h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-stone-600 mb-4 hidden md:block" aria-hidden="true">
          Core Values
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-16 md:gap-24">
        <div class="group border-t border-black/10 pt-12">
          <span class="text-sm font-mono text-stone-600 mb-8 block">01</span>
          <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light mb-6">Humanity</h3>
          <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
            A belief in the importance of warmth, sensitivity, and belonging in real life. A value that holds
            family, heart, and the desire to create relationships and spaces with softness, presence, and authenticity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group border-t border-black/10 pt-12">
          <span class="text-sm font-mono text-stone-600 mb-8 block">02</span>
          <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light mb-6">Truth</h3>
          <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
            It matters to me to work from honesty and loyalty to what feels genuinely right. True precision begins
            with integrity toward myself, toward my clients, and toward the process.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group border-t border-black/10 pt-12">
          <span class="text-sm font-mono text-stone-600 mb-8 block">03</span>
          <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light mb-6">Dedication</h3>
          <p class="text-xl text-stone-700 font-light leading-relaxed">
            I believe with my whole heart that if something is worth doing, it should be done fully and with the
            greatest possible depth, care, and commitment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="trust"
      class="py-32 md:py-40 px-8 md:px-16 bg-stone-50 border-t border-black/5"
      aria-labelledby="trust-heading"
    >
      <div class="max-w-[1800px] mx-auto">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-start gap-12 mb-20">
          <div class="max-w-3xl">
            <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-stone-600 mb-6 block">
              Trust Proof
            </span>
            <h2 id="trust-heading" class="text-4xl md:text-7xl font-light tracking-tighter leading-tight mb-8">
              Beauty is not enough.<br />
              It matters who you trust.
            </h2>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-2xl font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-700 max-w-2xl">
              The studio’s work rests on a rare combination of attentive human listening and proven experience with
              complex projects. The goal is to offer a precise, calm, and responsible process that remains professional
              even when working through constraints of time, budget, and execution.
            </p>
          </div>

          <a
            href="#contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-black/15 px-8 py-4 text-sm tracking-[0.18em] uppercase hover:bg-black hover:text-white transition-colors duration-500"
          >
            Book an intro call
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-20">
          {trustHighlights.map((item) => (
            <article class="border border-black/8 bg-white p-8 md:p-10">
              <span class="text-sm font-mono tracking-[0.18em] text-stone-500 mb-5 block">
                {item.label}
              </span>
              <p class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-light tracking-tight mb-5 font-cardo">{item.value}</p>
              <p class="text-lg font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-700">{item.description}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 xl:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
          {testimonials.map((testimonial) => (
            <article class="bg-white border border-black/8 overflow-hidden">
              <div class="aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden bg-stone-100">
                <img
                  src={testimonial.image}
                  alt={testimonial.imageAlt}
                  class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-[1.8s] hover:scale-105"
                />
              </div>

              <div class="p-8 md:p-10">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-stone-500 mb-6 block">
                  {testimonial.tag}
                </span>
                <blockquote class="text-lg md:text-[1.55rem] font-light leading-relaxed text-stone-800 mb-8">
                  “{testimonial.quote}”
                </blockquote>
                <div class="border-t border-black/8 pt-6">
                  <p class="text-xl font-medium">{testimonial.author}</p>
                  <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-stone-600 mt-2">
                    {testimonial.role}
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="services" class="py-32 border-t border-gray-100" aria-labelledby="services-heading">
      <div class="px-8 md:px-16 mb-24 flex justify-between items-end gap-8">
        <h2 id="services-heading" class="text-4xl md:text-8xl font-light tracking-tighter">Services</h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-stone-600 mb-4 hidden md:block" aria-hidden="true">
          Expertise
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="group border-t border-black/10 py-16 px-8 md:px-16 hover:bg-stone-50 transition-colors duration-500 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-baseline relative z-10">
            <span class="text-sm font-mono text-stone-600 mb-4 md:mb-0">01</span>
            <h3 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-light group-hover:translate-x-4 transition-transform duration-500">
              Interior design
            </h3>
            <p class="text-base text-stone-700 max-w-xs mt-4 md:mt-0 text-left">
              Thoughtful, fully considered interior planning
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="hidden md:block absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[400px] h-[300px] opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-all duration-500 pointer-events-none z-0 rotate-3 group-hover:rotate-0"
